\sum_{k=1}^{\infty} x^k =  \dfrac{x}{1-x} = \dfrac1{1-x} - 1
\sum_{k=1}^{\infty} kx^{k-1} = \dfrac1{(x-1)^2} \implies \sum_{k=1}^{\infty} kx^{k} = \dfrac{x}{(x-1)^2} = \dfrac1{x-1} + \dfrac1{(x-1)^2}
\sum_{k=1}^{\infty} k^2x^{k-1} = -\dfrac1{(x-1)^2} - \dfrac2{(x-1)^3}
